          <article class="faq-item">
            <button type="button" aria-expanded="false">Do you handle urgent drain or sewer calls?</button>
            <div><p>Yes. Emergency response is available for backups, overflowing drains, sewer issues, and other urgent drain or sewer problems.</p></div>
          </article>
          <article class="faq-item">
            <button type="button" aria-expanded="false">When do I need a camera inspection?</button>
            <div><p>A camera inspection is useful when clogs return, multiple fixtures are affected, a sewer line may be damaged, or a property transaction needs honest documentation.</p></div>
          </article>
          <article class="faq-item">
            <button type="button" aria-expanded="false">Is hydro jetting better than snaking?</button>
            <div><p>Snaking can open many clogs quickly. Hydro jetting is better suited for heavy buildup, grease, sludge, scale, and recurring restrictions that need a more complete cleaning.</p></div>
          </article>
          <article class="faq-item">
            <button type="button" aria-expanded="false">Do you work with commercial properties?</button>
            <div><p>Yes. The commercial page covers restaurants, facilities, multi-family properties, floor drains, storm drains, sewer cleaning, drain repairs, and maintenance programs.</p></div>
          </article>
          <article class="faq-item">
            <button type="button" aria-expanded="false">Can I request routine maintenance?</button>
            <div><p>Yes. Maintenance plans can be built around the property type, drain usage, prior backups, and the honest cost of downtime.</p></div>
          </article>
          <article class="faq-item">
            <button type="button" aria-expanded="false">What information should I include when booking?</button>
            <div><p>Share your address, the affected fixture or drain, when the problem started, whether it is getting worse, and whether more than one fixture is involved.</p></div>
